  "texts": [
    "First, providing extensive definitions of the DSA's key provisions, obligations, and timelines to situate these mechanisms.",
    "Second, articulating known critiques around the efficacy of the DSA's approach to curbing disinformation and broader policy aims.",
    "Third and centrally, proposing research approaches to shed lights over the DSA's impacts.The methods proposed for evaluating DSA impact on online disinformation can be directly extended to examine its role in shaping policy responses to emerging AI challenges.",
    "For instance, the DSA's provisions around algorithmic transparency and behavioral targeting disclosure address emerging social risks from AI \"black box\" systems.",
    "Similarly, its risk assessment and risk mitigation requirements for \"very large online platforms\" (VLOPs) could mitigate potential harms from highly scalable applications of generative AI if extended beyond social media.Far from thus providing definitive solutions, the intended contribution of this work stands in outlining a critical research agenda to inform incremental optimizations of the DSA based on empirically quantified, multidimensional insights into its provisions' efficacy.The rest of the paper is structured as follows."
  ],
